Keep Those Curtains Open To Kill Illness-Causing Bacteria: Study|http://www.huffingtonpost.ca|http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2018/10/19/sunshine-kills-bacteria_a_23565961/?utm_hp_ref=ca-homepage||2018-10-19|||LIVING

Keep Those Curtains Open To Kill Illness-Causing Bacteria: Study

A new study suggests sunlight can kill disease-causing bacteria that live in dust, so open curtains or windows in the home or office to ward off illness. Darker conditions can allow pathogens to thrive and even reproduce, according to the research.
